### 1. Create a Department - Engineering
POST http://localhost:8080/api/departments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Engineering"
}

### 2. Create a Department - HR
POST http://localhost:8080/api/departments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Human Resources"
}

### 3. Get All Departments
GET http://localhost:8080/api/departments

### 4. Create Employee - John Doe
POST http://localhost:8080/api/employees
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "role": "Senior Developer",
  "departmentId": 1
}

### 5. Create Employee - Jane Smith
POST http://localhost:8080/api/employees
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Jane Smith",
  "role": "HR Manager",
  "departmentId": 2
}

### 6. Get All Employees (with pagination)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/employees?page=0&size=10&sortBy=name&sortDir=asc

### 7. Search Employees by Name (John)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/employees?name=John

### 8. Search Employees by Department (Engineering = ID 1)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/employees?departmentId=1

### 9. Search Employees by Role containing "Developer"
GET http://localhost:8080/api/employees?role=Developer

### 10. Get Single Employee by ID
GET http://localhost:8080/api/employees/1

### 11. Update Employee (change name and role)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/employees/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe Updated",
  "role": "Tech Lead",
  "departmentId": 1
}

### 12. Delete Employee
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/employees/1